HEADWORD: Wilderment
<hw>Wil"der*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state of
being bewildered; confusion; bewilderment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And snatched her breathless from beneath⟦br⟧
This <qex>wilderment</qex> of wreck and death.</q>
<rj><qau>Moore.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wilderness</ent>⟦br⟧
